      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since you're having a lot of pain and instability, you need more than just RICE. You should immediately apply ice, but also take a very strong dose of ibuprofen, like 800mg, to manage the inflammation. For the best outcome, I strongly recommend applying a compression bandage and seeing a physiotherapist or getting an X-ray to rule out a fracture. Don't wait to see if it settles; get it checked out today!",
